' ---
' artifact-id: usecase-vs001-v1
' artifact-type: diagram
' name: "Value Stream: Forward SDLC — Use Case View"
' diagram-type: usecase
' version: 0.1.0
' status: draft
' phase-produced: B
' owner-agent: SA
' engagement: ENG-001
' domain: core-platform
' purpose: >
'   Stakeholder-facing view of VS-001 (Forward SDLC): the six stages through which
'   the SDLC multi-agent system delivers value to the User (engagement owner) and
'   to the Architecture Board. Each stage is shown as a use-case with the primary
'   business services (BSV) delivering value at that stage. Intended audience: PO,
'   user / engagement owner, Architecture Board.
' entity-ids-used:
'   - VS-001
'   - ACT-001
'   - BCO-001
'   - BSV-001
'   - BSV-002
'   - BSV-003
'   - BSV-004
'   - BSV-005
'   - BSV-006
'   - BSV-007
'   - BSV-008
'   - BSV-009
' ---
@startuml usecase-vs001-v1
!include ../_macros.puml
!include ../_archimate-stereotypes.puml
title Value Stream: Forward SDLC — Use Case View

left to right direction
skinparam usecase {
  BackgroundColor #FEFDF0
  BorderColor #B8860B
  ArrowColor #B8860B
  ActorBorderColor #4682B4
  ActorBackgroundColor #EEF4FF
}
skinparam usecaseBorderThickness 1.5
skinparam padding 10

' ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
' Actors
' ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
actor "User\n(Engagement Owner)" as ACT_001_uc
actor "Architecture Board\n(BCO-001)" as BCO_001_uc

' ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
' VS-001: Forward SDLC — all six stages as use cases
' ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
rectangle "VS-001: Forward SDLC" {

  usecase "**Stage 1**\nEngagement Scoping\n──────────────\nBSV-003 Project Coordination\nBSV-005 Requirements Mgmt" as S1
  usecase "**Stage 2**\nArchitecture Vision\n──────────────\nBSV-001 Business Architecture\nBSV-003 Project Coordination" as S2
  usecase "**Stage 3**\nArchitecture Design\n──────────────\nBSV-001 Business Architecture\nBSV-002 App & Tech Architecture\nBSV-005 Requirements Mgmt" as S3
  usecase "**Stage 4**\nDelivery Planning\n──────────────\nBSV-003 Project Coordination\nBSV-007 Quality Assurance\nBSV-008 Platform Engineering" as S4
  usecase "**Stage 5**\nSoftware Delivery\n──────────────\nBSV-006 Code Delivery\nBSV-007 Quality Assurance\nBSV-008 Platform Engineering" as S5
  usecase "**Stage 6**\nArchitecture Promotion\n──────────────\nBSV-001 Business Architecture\nBSV-002 App & Tech Architecture\nBSV-004 Safety Governance" as S6

}

' ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
' Relationships
' ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
' User participates in all 6 stages
ACT_001_uc --> S1 : initiates
ACT_001_uc --> S2 : receives\nArchitecture Vision
ACT_001_uc --> S3 : reviews &\nconfirms design
ACT_001_uc --> S4 : approves\ndelivery plan
ACT_001_uc --> S5 : receives\ndelivered software
ACT_001_uc --> S6 : authorises\npromotion

' Architecture Board participates in Stage 6 (promotion authority)
BCO_001_uc --> S6 : governs\nenterprise promotion

' Value flows between stages (sequential)
S1 .> S2 : <<include>>
S2 .> S3 : <<include>>
S3 .> S4 : <<include>>
S4 .> S5 : <<include>>
S5 .> S6 : <<include>>

note bottom of S6
  Stage 6 occurs at VS-001 completion.
  Also triggered by Brownfield engagements
  that reach full architecture reconstruction.
end note

@enduml
